f=Cybersecurity/cortex/marketplace/detection-engineering/SKILL.md · in=Elastic Security MCP provides capabilities SOC analysts detection engineers investigate, triage, respond security alerts, manage detection rules, conduct attack discovery analysis. skill integrates Elastic Security's APIs provide comprehensive security operations workflow. · h3:1. Alert Triage=Fetch investigate security alerts Elastic Security, Classify threats determine severity, Create cases confirmed incidents, Investigate alert context related events · h3:2. Detection Rule Management=Create new detection rules (query-based, threshold, machine learning, ESQL), Tune existing rules reduce false positives, Add exceptions rules based investigation findings, Manage rule timing schedule · h3:3. Attack Discovery=Correlate alerts attack narratives, Assess confidence based entity risk rule frequency, Map findings MITRE ATT&CK framework, Provide timeline reconstruction attack sequences · h3:4. Sample Event Generation=Generate synthetic security events testing detection rules, Validate rule behavior before production deployment, Create test datasets benchmark testing · wu=Triage incoming security alerts determine severity, Create modify detection rules based threat intelligence, Investigate potential security incidents entity context, Reduce false positive rates tuning rules, Test detection coverage sample events, Conduct attack discovery analysis across correlated alerts · h3:Alert Triage Workflow=Fetch recent alerts Elastic Security (by severity, time range, rule type) Investigate alert: check event details, related entities, historical context Classify as: true positive, false positive, needs further investigation true positives: open case, add observables, assign analyst false positives: consider adding exception tuning rule Document findings update alert status · h3:Detection Rule Management Workflow=Identify detection gaps (missing coverage known TTPs) Create rules using appropriate type (query, threshold, ML, ESQL) Test rules against historical data Enable monitor rule performance Review tune regularly based false positive rates · h3:Attack Discovery Workflow=Start suspicious entity (host, user, IP) Pull related alerts events Correlate events timeline Map MITRE ATT&CK techniques Assess confidence based evidence strength Recommend next steps investigation containment · of=`## Detection Analysis: [alert/entity/rule] \· Type: [triage / rule-management / attack-discovery / event-generation] \· Finding: [description of what was discovered or configured] \· Confidence: [assessment based on evidence strength] \· MITRE ATT&CK: [technique IDs if applicable]` · pr=**Triage thoroughly, classify decisively** alert gets investigated; ambiguous findings escalated, set aside. **False positives data, noise** opportunity tune rule close detection gap. **Test before deploying** never enable detection rule without validating against historical data. **Correlation over isolation** single alert signal; correlated alerts tell story. **Document everything** alert investigations, rule changes, tuning decisions logged.